Guidelines for FHA approved condos for borrowers

    Credit score of 620 or higher. The borrower will need decent credit rating. People that have declared bankruptcy have to wait 2 yrs before you apply for a FHA loan.
    Deposit. The borrower have to have a down payment, set at around 5% from the total sales price.
    History of employment. The borrower can show two years of employment history in any industry.
    Legal Documents. The borrower will need their social security number, tax documents, and valid identification.

